This too will pass … and motorsport will survive in South Africa. That message comes from maestro Sarel van der Merwe who, at the age of 74, is still arguably the best known name in South African motorsport annals. Even though the coronavirus pandemic has halted all sporting activities across the globe, Van der Merwe strongly believes it isn’t a death blow for internationally or local motorsport despite the impending economic recession.  These days, at the age of 74, Van der Merwe is still highly competitive in the top echelons of local Historic car racing. “Right...